TextBody:
Hello Kristen,

Let me know if we can schedule a remote session for Thursday or Friday in order to investigate this.
I will have to ssh on the EPP Server in order to investigate what can cause the issue. In order to be able to ssh on the server during our remote session, you will have to allow the port 62828 for the EPP Server in AWS (the port can be opened only for your IP).
Probably the server does not have enough resources for the amount of computers where the EPP Client is installed or the resources are not optimized.

Best regards,
Emil
